    • Constructor Detail

      • DiffUtils

        public DiffUtils(BeanMatcher beanMatcher)
        Contruct a new shallow DiffUtils. By default when comparing beans or fields links and array properties will not be deeply traversed. For example, if two links point to beans that are logically equal then the beans will not be inspected. To increase the depth of the comparison use setMaxDepth and/or setDeepCompare.
        Parameters:
        beanMatcher - Code to compare two beans to check if they're the same logical bean

      • doBeansMatch

        public boolean doBeansMatch(KeyableBean b1,
                            KeyableBean b2)
        Determine if two beans are really the same "thing", e.g. they are the same logical entity. Used by compareField when matching up array elements to see which are added, removed, or changed, and to see if two links point to the same logical entity vs. different entities.
        Specified by:
        doBeansMatch in interface BeanMatcher
        Parameters:
        b1 - Source bean
        b2 - Compare bean
        Returns:
        True if the beans are logically equivalent. For exampe, 2 people are logicall equal if they have the same SSN. 2 coverages are logicall equal if they share the same pattern.
